<TEXT>
china suspended diplomatic relations with lesotho 
on saturday two days after the small african nation established 
ties with taiwan 
the official xinhua news agency had reported in english that 
beijing decided to break off relations with lesotho but this 
appeared to be a mistranslation 
chineselanguage reports said beijing suspended ties as it has 
with three other small countries that recently recognized taiwan 
grenada liberia and belize 
china accused lesotho of violating its pledge to recognize the 
peoples republic of china as the sole legal government of china 
taiwan an island province of china is governed by the 
nationalists who fled the mainland in 1949 after being defeated by 
the communists in a civil war the nationalists still claim to be 
the rightful rulers of all china 
lesotho a kingdom with a population of 16 million surrounded 
by south africa established relations with beijing in 1983 
</TEXT>
