abc cbs nbc and cnn plan to televise the 
scheduled launch of the shuttle discovery live tuesday morning 
the spacecraft is scheduled to lift off at 847 am edt from 
the kennedy space center at cape canaveral fla 
during the fiveday trip into space five astronauts will put 
into orbit the hubble space telescope which will give scientists a 
look at stars and galaxies light years away 
cnn plans to begin coverage from the space center at 530 am 
edt tuesday according to a statement issued by cnn 
abcs coverage will begin during good morning america and 
then go to a special report according to arnot walker an abc 
spokesman 
cbs will carry the liftoff live as part of its cbs this 
morning news show said tina wynn a spokeswoman for cbs 
nbc will air the launch on the today morning news show said 
nbc spokeswoman katherine mcquay 
