slovenia is the first of yugoslavias six republics to hold free 
elections 
yugoslavia is a loose federation of six republics and two 
autonomous provinces it is ruled by an eightman collective 
presidency 
communist leaders have allowed the formation of opposition 
parties in all of the republics but only croatia the 
secondlargest republic has also scheduled multiparty elections 
those elections are planned for april 
communist leaders in serbia the largest republic have demanded 
communist party dominance and have harshly criticized the reforms 
in slovenia 
