the conservative new democracy party 
claimed victory sunday after it captured about half the seats in 
greeces third parliamentary election in 10 months 
but it remained uncertain if the party would win the outright 
majority that would enable it to break the countrys political 
deadlock without help from outside its ranks 
returns showed new democracy which barely missed majorities in 
the inconclusive elections last june and november had won at least 
150 of the 300 seats in parliament 
