the first round of elections on march 25 put the hungarian 
democratic forum and the liberal alliance of free democrats in the 
lead but neither party polled a majority forcing sundays second 
round 
the socialists were unique among ruling soviet bloc parties in 
leading their country to democracy without massive popular 
pressure but most people associate the party with the excesses of 
43 years of communist rule 
the free democrats have warmed in recent weeks to the 
possibility of a coalition with the democratic forum 
but the forum has said it will only join forces with the free 
democrats in a national emergency 
antall refused to comment when asked sunday about the 
possibility of a coalition government with the free democrats 
but free democrat leader janos kis said that a grand coalition 
is a distinct possibility which we dont refuse because we are 
for having a government with wide popular support 
