fire broke out monday on a car ferry carrying 297 
people from britains west coast to ireland killing a crew member 
and injuring nine people officials said 
the fire broke out beneath the car deck as the b and i ferry 
norrano was eight miles west of the welsh coast the coast guard 
said spokesman george clarke said the fire was brought under 
control 
a royal air force spokesman said one crew member had been killed 
clarke said the injured including a pregnant women were 
suffering from smoke inhalation he said they had been evacuated to 
withybush hospital in haverford west by three raf helicopters 
the first helicopter brought out eight firefighters and then 
we brought out two doctors with oxygen equipment clarke said 
the ferry carrying 78 crew members and 219 passengers was en 
route from milford haven 180 miles west of london to rosslare 
ireland 
the coast guard spokesman said the vessel was returning to 
milford haven under its own power 
